.TH "lpfc_debugfs_dumpHostSlim_data" 9 "lpfc_debugfs_dumpHostSlim_data" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_debugfs_dumpHostSlim_data \- Dump host SLIM info to a buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" lpfc_debugfs_dumpHostSlim_data
.BI "(struct lpfc_hba *phba "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "int size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "phba" 12
The HBA to gather Host SLIM info from.
.IP "buf" 12
The buffer to dump log into.
.IP "size" 12
The maximum amount of data to process.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine dumps the current contents of host SLIM for the host associated
with \fIphba\fP to \fIbuf\fP up to \fIsize\fP bytes of data. The dump will contain the
Mailbox, PCB, Rings, and Registers that are located in host memory.

Return Value:
This routine returns the amount of bytes that were dumped into \fIbuf\fP and will
not exceed \fIsize\fP.
